cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language inference tasks and word vector representation models, which are commonly studied in the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of knowledge graphs and entity-attribute-relationship graphs, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV).
